{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix buffer overflow in logicalChannelBearer configuration\n\n### Summary\nThe NR UE MAC layer contained a buffer overflow vulnerability in the `nr_rrc_mac_config_req_ue_logicalChannelBearer` function. The function was using the `logicalChannelIdentity` parameter directly as an array index without bounds checking, which could lead to out-of-bounds memory writes.\n\nThe vulnerability could be triggered by malformed RRC configuration messages containing invalid logical channel identity values. Under certain conditions, this could lead to memory corruption and potential remote code execution.\n\nThe issue was fixed by adding proper bounds checking before using the `logicalChannelIdentity` parameter as an array index.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/config_ue.c`: Added bounds checking in `nr_rrc_mac_config_req_ue_logicalChannelBearer` function to prevent buffer overflow when configuring logical channel bearers.\n\n"
}